    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-06-09T18:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-06-09T18:14:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/6–953: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-06-09T19:14:00-04:00"
                            >June 9, 1953—7:14 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>782. Re Chinese representation. We must prepare for possibility question of
                    seating Chinese Communists will be raised in <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1"
                        >ECOSOC</gloss> meeting in Geneva where we will be represented by
                    inexperienced man. Plans should be made now to provide him with necessary help
                    to deal with such attempt. All other meetings which are being held in New York
                    can be covered by me as need arises. My present feeling, subject to further
                    thought, is that <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> is most advantageous place
                    for us in which to have Chinese Communist representation question raised because
                    I will be presiding and veto can be used in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.
                    For this reason I am considering advisability of calling meeting of <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> to communicate to its members armistice
                    terms.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
